TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
IMAGE;VALUE=URI;DISPLAY=BADGE;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.levyparkhousto
 n.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/IMG_4987.jpeg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.levyparkhouston.org/wp-content/upload
 s/2026/05/IMG_4987.jpeg
UID:_yX20uHWQRfw2tYIRgVVA
SUMMARY:Free Watch Party: South Africa vs. Canada
DTSTAMP:20260628T101703Z
DTSTART:20260628T123000Z
DESCRIPTION:The group stage is done and the knockout rounds are here! Thirt
	y-two teams still standing\, all of them hungry\, none of them ready to go
	 home. Tonight the tournament gets real. Join us as the first teams punch 
	their tickets to the Round of 16. \nFestival gates open at 12:30 p.m. to t
	he music of DJ Cris. Kickoff is at 2:00 p.m. Admission is free! \nFood and
	 Beverage Concessions: Enjoy a variety of festival food fare\, beer and wi
	ne\, and non-alcoholic beverages from Coca-Cola. Visit Smalls Sliders for 
	burgers\, fries\, and shakes and cool down with Frios Gourmet Pops. Stop b
	y Hearsay’s festival tent for a cold beer or beer bucket or grab a michela
	da\, wine\, or beer from Gaspacho’s festival tent. Non-alcoholic drinks fr
	om Coca-Cola as well as pre-packaged snacks can be purchased at the Commun
	ity Partner Concessions Booth\, proceeds benefiting Levy Park and the even
	t’s community partners. \nCommunity Partner: We are proud to be joined by 
	our Community Partner\, Dynamo & Dash Charities\, for this event! By lever
	aging the passion of players\, staff\, and fans\, Dynamo & Dash Charities 
	provides resources and education to positively impact lives in the communi
	ty. Stop by the Community Partner Booth to support their amazing work and 
	learn more about their initiatives. All food & beverage proceeds from the 
	Community Partner booth will support Dynamo & Dash Charities and Levy Park
	. \nFace Painting & Henna Art: Get into the tournament spirit with face an
	d body art from Butterfly Faces by Shondra Macklin and Henna Station & Gli
	tter Bar \nMerchandise: Event merchandise celebrating Houston\, Levy Park\
	, and the global soccer tournament will also be available for purchase. \n
	Art Installations and Photo Opportunities: Commemorate the experience with
	 a photo tour of the park\, including life-sized soccer-themed photo backd
	rops and a tournament bracket. Visit our soccer ball music box and turn th
	e crank for festive sounds. \nFestival Guidelines: \nVISITORS MUST COMPLY 
	WITH DIRECTIONS FROM PARK PERSONNEL\, OR THEY WILL BE ASKED TO LEAVE THE P
	ARK. PARENTS ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR THEIR CHILDREN’S SAFETY IN THE PARK. \nCH
	AIRS AND SEATING: No outside furniture. Blankets may be brought into the F
	estival site for the designated blanket seating area. All other furniture 
	is available on a first-come\, first-served basis. \nSTROLLERS & WAGONS: O
	versized strollers and wagons may need to be parked in a designated area d
	uring the festival. All visitors must comply with park personnel regarding
	 stroller and wagon parking. \nFOOD AND BEVERAGES: Guests are permitted to
	 enter with one factory-sealed bottle of water. Outside food and drinks ar
	e prohibited (exceptions will be made for baby food and necessary medical 
	dietary food items). A variety of food\, non-alcoholic drinks\, beer\, and
	 wine will be available for purchase from Festival concessionaires. \nRE-E
	NTRY: If you leave the Festival site\, you will be re-screened before re-e
	ntry. \nTHE FOLLOWING ARE PROHIBITED: \n\nSmoking or Vaping\nUmbrellas\nDr
	ug Use\nKites and Drones\nRecreational Motorized Vehicles\nGuns\, knives\,
	 any weaponry\nSoliciting\nBikes\, scooters\, rollerblades\, and roller sk
	ates\n\nhttps://www.levyparkhouston.org/events/round-of-32-game-1/\n\nFrom
	 Levy Park Houston
URL:https://www.levyparkhouston.org/events/round-of-32-game-1/
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:levy-park-houston
CATEGORIES:Levy Park Houston
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT5H
END:VEVENT
